{
  "texts": [
    "Nevertheless, this decrease must be carefully monitored to guarantee that crucial information is preserved for precise classification.",
    "Excess reduction in dimensionality could result in the elimination of essential features that have discriminatory information, causing problems with the model's capacity to correctly categorize samples.",
    "Conversely, keeping an excessive number of features may add interference and result in the model becoming excessively intricate, thus impeding its ability to generalize to unfamiliar data.",
    "Choosing the correct balance requires the selection of suitable dimensionality reduction methods depending on the data's attributes.",
    "Parameter tuning is necessary to regulate the level of reduction and preserve the most pertinent information."
  ]
}